# API Client Rules

## Every function MUST have a matching backend endpoint
```
apiClient.get('/items')    → @Get() in items.controller.ts
apiClient.post('/items')   → @Post() in items.controller.ts
apiClient.patch('/items')  → @Patch() in items.controller.ts
apiClient.delete('/items') → @Delete() in items.controller.ts
```
Frontend call without backend endpoint = 404 at runtime.

## Use typed responses
```typescript
export async function getItems(): Promise<Item[]> {
  const response = await apiClient.get('/items');
  return response.data;
}
```

## Match HTTP methods to operations
- GET = read (list, get by id)
- POST = create
- PATCH = update
- DELETE = remove
